{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"@"},{"kind":"attribute","text":"MainActor","preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"OUDSBulletList"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"mentions":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/ContentDisplay"],"kind":"mentions"},{"content":[{"anchor":"Types","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Types"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Three types are proposed:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Unordered (by default)","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": Collects related items that don’t need to be in a specific order or sequence."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Ordered","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": Collects related items with numeric order or sequence."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Bare","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": An unordered list without any bullets or alphanumeric sequence."}]}]}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Types can be mixed in list, but must be identical for the same ","type":"text"},{"code":"OUDSBulletList.NestedLevel","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Levels","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Levels"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Lists can include nested items to indicate hierarchy or subcategories, with indentation distinguishing each level.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Arrange ordered list items logically, such as ranking by importance, highest to lowest values, or in alphabetical \/ numeric order.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Three levels are maximum.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Text-Style","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Text Style"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"List can be used with different font sizes:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Body Large"}]},{"text":": If the text accompanying the list component is the Body Large text. This variant is designed for more visual, engaging experiences.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Body Medium","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":": If the text accompanying the list component is the Body Medium text. This variant is best suited for functional, task-oriented experiences."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"anchor":"Cases-forbidden-by-design","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Cases forbidden by design"},{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"it is not allowed to have a depth of items greater than 3","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Internationalisation-considerations","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Internationalisation considerations"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"For latin-based speaking countries, like France, Spain, United Kingdom or Belgium, the european “arabic” numbers are used for the first level of depth","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"of the ordered bullet list. For the second and third levels, the european alphabets are used with upper and lower case values.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"However for countries speaking arabic, these rules can’t be applied. Indeed, there is no notion of upper and lower case characters in arabic alphabet."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"In addition, the numbers in use (i.e. the european “arabic” numbers like “1, 2, 3”) are accepted in arabic countries, even if the “true arabic” numbers (like “ ٢ ٣ ١”) are used"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in middle-east arabic countries and for official documents."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Thus the OUDS ordered bullet list will use “european” numbers for first level, and arabic alphabets for second and third levels."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Code-samples","text":"Code samples","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["       \/\/ 1. Unordered list with bullets","       OUDSBulletList {","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 1\")","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 2\")","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 3\")","       }","","       \/\/ 1.1. Item of Unordered list with bullet as tick, a text style","       \/\/ body medium and text bold","       OUDSBulletList(type: .unordered(asset: .tick),","                      textStyle: .bodyMedium,","                      isBold: true)  {","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 1\")","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 2\")","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 3\")","       }","","       \/\/ 2. Bare list with 3 items","       OUDSBulletList(type: .bare) {","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 1\")","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 2\")","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 3\")","       }","","       \/\/ 3. Ordered list with 3 items","       OUDSBulletList(type: .ordered) {","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 1\")","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 2\")","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 3\")","       }","","       \/\/ 3.1. Ordered list with 3 items in first level,","       \/\/ and one item as sub item (second level),","       \/\/ and 2 items as sub item in (third level)","       OUDSBulletList(type: .ordered) {","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 1\") {","               OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 1.1\") {","                   OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 1.1.1\")","                   OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 1.1.2\")","               }","           }","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 2\")","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 3\")","       }","","       \/\/ Same Bullet list but items in third level with free icon as bullet","       let icon = Image(decorative: \"ic_heart\")","       OUDSBulletList(type: .ordered) {","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 1\") {","               OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 1.1\", subListType: .unordered(asset: .icon(icon))) {","                   OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 1.1.1\")","                   OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 1.1.2\")","               }","           }","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 2\")","           OUDSBulletList.Item(\"Label 3\")","       }"],"syntax":"swift"},{"anchor":"Rich-text","text":"Rich text","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Rich text can be applied only if ","type":"text"},{"code":"isBold","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" flag is set to ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"false"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Strong text can be used sparingly within alert messages to highlight key information."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Underlined text must not be used for emphasis, as it is commonly associated with links."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"If a hyperlink is needed within the content, the underlined style should be used."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Italic should be used with care, some brands do not allow it like Orange brand."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"No other text styles should be used."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Accessibility-considerations","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Accessibility considerations"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Always check the results of rich text mode with high contrast, light and dark modes, and Voice Over vocalization."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Design-documentation","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Design documentation"},{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/r.orange.fr\/r\/S-ouds-doc-bullet-list","type":"reference"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Themes-rendering","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Themes rendering"},{"anchor":"Orange","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Orange"},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_bullet_list_Orange","type":"image"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Orange-Compact","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Orange Compact"},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_bullet_list_OrangeCompact","type":"image"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Sosh","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Sosh"},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_bullet_list_Sosh","type":"image"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Wireframe","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Wireframe"},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_bullet_list_Wireframe","type":"image"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"name":"Version","type":"aside","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"1.0.0 (Figma component design version)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"style":"note"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"1.2.0"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"aside","style":"note","name":"Since"}],"kind":"content"}],"kind":"symbol","variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/oudscomponents\/oudsbulletlist"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents"]]},"sections":[],"metadata":{"symbolKind":"struct","modules":[{"name":"Components"}],"roleHeading":"Structure","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"OUDSBulletList","kind":"identifier"}],"externalID":"s:14OUDSComponents14OUDSBulletListV","title":"OUDSBulletList","platforms":[{"beta":false,"unavailable":false,"name":"iOS","introducedAt":"15.0","deprecated":false},{"beta":false,"unavailable":false,"name":"macOS","introducedAt":"13.0","deprecated":false},{"beta":false,"unavailable":false,"name":"tvOS","introdu